<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FRONT DRIVE AXLE WHEEL ENDS: FABCO SDA-12 - DIFFERENTIAL CARRIER - INSTALL TO AXLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSTALL TO AXLE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Refer to the Differential Carrier Service Manual for detailed service procedures.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a bead of liquid sealant to the differential mounting face. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s02010_24.xml" xrefid="hl0201007">GENERAL PRECAUTIONS</hotlnk>
                (Item #1). Apply in the same manner as shown in
                <hotlnk document="s02010_24.xml" xrefid="f0201043">Figure 43</hotlnk>
                for the axle flanges; a bead and a ring around each bolt hole.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the differential carrier in the axle housing with a suitable roller jack, picking
                up two locating studs (refer to
                <hotlnk document="s02010_36.xml" xrefid="f0201045">Figure 45</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install differential carrier capscrews and stud nuts. Tighten to 45 - 55 ft-lbs. (60 - 75 N&#183;m).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the propeller shaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the drain plug and fill the axle to the bottom edge of the level hole with the
                appropriate lubricant. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s02010_38.xml" xrefid="hl0201010">LUBRICATION</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the level plug.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
